sub_title: UWCSEA Alumna | BSc International Economics and Business Economics at Utrecht University ‘25 | BSc Computer Science at Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam '25
summary:
Hello!

I am Anna Wischnewski, student at Utrecht University and Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam. I am thoroughly invested in economics, finance, and development, as well as computer science, technology and innovation. 

I balance my academic interests with a passion for extracurricular activities. Currently, I am the President of the Student Council of the Science Faculty at VU, the President of the student organisation Women in STEM at VU, and the President of the Career Committee of ESN Utrecht.

I am employed as a Customer Engagement Associate II at Conduent, where we support smart Europe. My tasks are social media management and mobility consultation as part of the Customer Engagement Centre. 

If you would like to learn more about my current projects, past experiences and my up-to-date CV, I invite you to check out annawischnewski.com
